Well. there's no way
I'm learning your first name now.

245
00:12:48.143 --> 00:12:50.395
I think it's time for me
to stop hiding from the future.

246
00:12:50.979 --> 00:12:52.439
Okay. that sucks.

247
00:12:52.523 --> 00:12:55.150
Are you really gonna pretend
this is super serious to you?

248
00:12:55.234 --> 00:12:56.944
Nah. But...

249
00:12:59.029 --> 00:13:00.322
I am gonna miss it.

250
00:13:00.405 --> 00:13:03.075
Well. I didn't say
it had to end this second.

251
00:13:03.784 --> 00:13:06.078
So we doing the grand finale type thing?

252
00:13:06.745 --> 00:13:09.039
Doing the gospel choir with the...
fireworks?

253
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:10.749
Yeah. but I gotta be at work in 15.

254
00:13:10.832 --> 00:13:13.961
I can do a no-frills ten.
Come here. Dr. Sykes.

255
00:13:14.044 --> 00:13:16.964
No shit. She really broke up with you?

256
00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:18.131
Yeah.

257
00:13:19.466 --> 00:13:20.676
You seem surprised?

258
00:13:20.759 --> 00:13:22.928
Only because she hasn't called me yet.

259
00:13:24.096 --> 00:13:27.057
We talked about it more.
and she said that being with me

260
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:28.600
was keeping her from moving forward.

261
00:13:29.768 --> 00:13:32.229
I understand it. but it's still annoying.

262
00:13:32.312 --> 00:13:34.940
Well. maybe it's annoying
because deep down you realize

263
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:36.942
that you should be moving on too.

264
00:13:37.025 --> 00:13:38.735
I know you want more.

265
00:13:39.611 --> 00:13:42.781
A real relationship. your own place.

266
00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:45.075
a sailboat in Connecticut.

267
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:48.453
Okay. the last one's mine.

268
00:13:48.537 --> 00:13:53.250
But point is.
if you're not growing. you're not living.

269
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:55.043
Nah. I lived this morning.

270
00:13:55.127 --> 00:13:56.128
Twice.

271
00:13:56.211 --> 00:13:58.130
I'll make a note of that.

272
00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:03.218
Patient keeps bragging
despite having been dumped.

273
00:14:04.136 --> 00:14:05.262
I miss the notebook.

274
00:14:05.846 --> 00:14:06.930
So do I. kid.

275
00:14:07.014 --> 00:14:09.224
My handwriting got too shaky.

276
00:14:10.142 --> 00:14:12.519
Have I taught you about The Field?

277
00:14:13.103 --> 00:14:15.856
Is this more of
your crunchy munchy spiritual crap?

278
00:14:15.939 --> 00:14:18.859
Life is a conversation with the universe.

279
00:14:18.942 --> 00:14:20.360
And we're off.

280
00:14:20.444 --> 00:14:26.116
The Field is an intelligent energy force
that knows who you're supposed to be.

281
00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:31.622
And it's gonna keep demonstrating to you
what it is you need to work on most.

282
00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:35.334
Over and over again
until you start to do it.

283
00:14:35.417 --> 00:14:36.418
Damn.

284
00:14:37.044 --> 00:14:39.880
That actually sounds like
it would be very helpful

285
00:14:40.422 --> 00:14:41.423
if it were real.

286
00:14:42.799 --> 00:14:43.884
Why are you smiling?

287
00:14:44.468 --> 00:14:46.970
Because I'm just thinking about
how much I'm gonna enjoy it

288
00:14:47.054 --> 00:14:49.723
when you find out that Field is real.

289
00:14:50.349 --> 00:14:51.934
And when that happens.

290
00:14:52.017 --> 00:14:54.311
you don't even have to tell me
I was right.

291
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.438
Just. I don't know.

292
00:14:57.231 --> 00:14:59.691
throw me some prayer hands

293
00:15:01.026 --> 00:15:02.402
like I'm a god.

294
00:15:03.946 --> 00:15:06.031
How about I hit you with a sexy wink?

295
00:15:07.491 --> 00:15:08.867
You call that sexy?

296
00:15:09.451 --> 00:15:10.953
Okay. Let me see your game.

297
00:15:16.208 --> 00:15:17.251
All right. I'd hit that.

298
00:15:17.334 --> 00:15:18.710
You couldn't handle it.

299
00:15:20.629 --> 00:15:24.132
It's a lot redoing
the upstairs guest bathroom.

300
00:15:24.842 --> 00:15:29.054
And I appreciate that my husband's
giving me carte blanche budget wise.

301
00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:34.226
But every time I try to tell him
what I want to do creatively.

302
00:15:34.768 --> 00:15:36.103
he doesn't wanna hear it.

303
00:15:36.186 --> 00:15:37.938
Brave women are often silenced. Kathy.

304
00:15:38.856 --> 00:15:41.817
You. Rosa Parks. Pussy Riot...

305
00:15:43.402 --> 00:15:45.112
<i>Yeah. and I know
I shouldn't have said that.</i>

306
00:15:45.195 --> 00:15:48.282
But her problem just felt so trivial.
I couldn't stay focused.

307
00:15:48.365 --> 00:15:50.158
Man. I zone out sometimes too.

308
00:15:50.242 --> 00:15:52.452
I got this one patient. Gregory.

309
00:15:52.536 --> 00:15:53.662
He goes by Spider.

310
00:15:53.745 --> 00:15:56.290
He's got the great nickname.
he's covered in tats.

311
00:15:56.373 --> 00:15:58.000
He's always wearing some cool boots.

312
00:15:58.083 --> 00:16:01.336
This guy is so fucking boring--

313
00:16:02.087 --> 00:16:03.589
Hey. am I early?

314
00:16:03.672 --> 00:16:04.673
Gregory?

315
00:16:05.591 --> 00:16:08.135
Hey. man. How goes it?

316
00:16:08.719 --> 00:16:10.637
- We're gonna go do this.
- Yeah. go.

317
00:16:11.555 --> 00:16:13.849
Every time I doubt myself as a therapist.

318
00:16:13.932 --> 00:16:17.811
he goes and does something so stupid
that it makes me feel better about myself.

319
00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:19.730
That's why I keep him around.

320
00:16:19.813 --> 00:16:22.357
Yeah. You know.
everybody I've been treating these days

321
00:16:22.441 --> 00:16:24.484
just seems to be caught up
in such low-stakes shit.

322
00:16:24.568 --> 00:16:26.069
I know. suffering is suffering.

323
00:16:26.570 --> 00:16:28.864
And I'm grateful to make a living
doing what we do.

324
00:16:28.947 --> 00:16:30.073
But...

325
00:16:30.824 --> 00:16:33.869
I don't know. That stuff with my sister.
my dad being bipolar.

326
00:16:34.620 --> 00:16:38.040
Like. I got into this because I wanted
to help people deal with real trauma.

327
00:16:39.583 --> 00:16:42.711
Like. sometimes I just feel like I'm not
doing what I'm supposed to be doing.

328
00:16:42.794 --> 00:16:43.837
Does that make any sense?

329
00:16:45.422 --> 00:16:47.633
My first job was at Bellevue.

330
00:16:47.716 --> 00:16:53.263
Suicidal ideation. personality disorders.
schizophrenia. all of it.

331
00:16:53.347 --> 00:16:54.473
How was it?

332
00:16:54.556 --> 00:16:56.642
It was the worst job I ever had.

333
00:16:56.725 --> 00:16:59.645
- Really?
- And also the best.

334
00:17:00.854 --> 00:17:02.481
You'd be great there.

335
00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:05.275
Thanks. Paul.

336
00:17:05.358 --> 00:17:06.818
As a doctor.

337
00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:10.696
- or as a patient.
- Whatever.

338
00:17:10.781 --> 00:17:13.407
Okay. I've been thinking
about the color scheme in your nursery.

339
00:17:13.492 --> 00:17:16.869
For the curtains. I have two swatches
for you to choose from.

340
00:17:16.954 --> 00:17:19.540
- Tell him the truth.
- I have one swatch.

341
00:17:19.623 --> 00:17:21.290
- Okay.
- But I'm really excited

342
00:17:21.375 --> 00:17:22.917
- to hear your thoughts.
- Truth.

343
00:17:23.001 --> 00:17:25.838
I don't care what you think.
and I also chose the wallpaper.

344
00:17:25.921 --> 00:17:29.258
Okay. You know. actually.
Ava is coming to see us tomorrow.

345
00:17:29.341 --> 00:17:31.468
She might have some fun thoughts
decor-wise.

346
00:17:31.552 --> 00:17:33.637
You know.
Derek's brother used to eat candles.

347
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.055
What?

348
00:17:35.138 --> 00:17:37.683
I thought we were talking about
stupid shit that doesn't matter.

349
00:17:37.766 --> 00:17:40.185
Okay. Just show me the baby's wallpaper.

350
00:17:40.269 --> 00:17:42.104
Not yet.
The most important person isn't here.

351
00:17:42.187 --> 00:17:44.439
Rude. I told you Charlie couldn't make it.

352
00:17:44.523 --> 00:17:46.775
- Who gives a shit about Charlie?
- What's up. sluts?

353
00:17:46.859 --> 00:17:48.402
- Hey!
- Hello.

354
00:17:48.485 --> 00:17:50.279
Now we can begin.

355
00:17:51.864 --> 00:17:54.032
So. what do you think?

356
00:17:54.116 --> 00:17:55.325
It's so peaceful--

357
00:17:55.409 --> 00:17:56.535
Don't interrupt Gaby.

358
00:17:56.618 --> 00:17:58.245
I can't interrupt her
while she's thinking?

359
00:17:58.328 --> 00:18:00.747
- Brian. please! Damn.
- Okay. All right. I'm sorry.

360
00:18:01.999 --> 00:18:03.000
Liz. I love it.

361
00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:04.585
It's so peaceful.

362
00:18:04.668 --> 00:18:07.671
Plus. if you're feeling lazy. you don't
want to take the baby for a walk.

363
00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:11.133
you can just be like. "Look up at the sky.
baby. We're already outside."

364
00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:12.551
Babies are dumb.

365
00:18:12.634 --> 00:18:15.262
Can you believe she thinks she gets to
make these decisions about my baby.

366
00:18:15.345 --> 00:18:17.848
You knew what you was getting into
when you hired Nanny Mc-Liz.

367
00:18:17.931 --> 00:18:22.477
I made it perfectly clear you would be
dealing with a major control freak.

368
00:18:22.561 --> 00:18:23.937
I'm the worst.

369
00:18:27.566 --> 00:18:29.359
I'm just... I must take this out back.

370
00:18:31.236 --> 00:18:32.529
Hey. you.

371
00:18:32.613 --> 00:18:33.614
What was that about?

372
00:18:33.697 --> 00:18:34.698
I don't know.

373
00:18:34.781 --> 00:18:37.784
The past few days.
he's been taking secret calls.

374
00:18:37.868 --> 00:18:38.869
It's so weird.

375
00:18:38.952 --> 00:18:40.954
Usually. he answers the phone
on speaker phone.

376
00:18:41.038 --> 00:18:43.874
and makes everyone say hi
to whoever it is on the line.

377
00:18:43.957 --> 00:18:45.000
It makes me crazy.

378
00:18:45.083 --> 00:18:46.627
Obviously. he's revenge cheating on you.

379
00:18:46.710 --> 00:18:48.545
- What?
- Yes. the one-year rule.

380
00:18:48.629 --> 00:18:51.507
He gets that much time to do the same
thing you did with no consequences.

381
00:18:53.467 --> 00:18:54.468
Liz?

382
00:18:55.886 --> 00:18:57.054
Damn. dude. You broke her.

383
00:18:57.137 --> 00:19:00.307
- Liz. I was joking. It was just a joke.
- Hey. Come back. girl. Come back.

384
00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:02.226
Hey. hey! Come on!
We got a soccer game to get to.

385
00:19:02.309 --> 00:19:05.103
- That's right. Let's go! Let's go.
- Let's go! Let's go!

386
00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:07.523
- Let's do it! Let's do it.
- Let's go! Let's go.

387
00:19:07.606 --> 00:19:09.191
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

388
00:19:09.274 --> 00:19:10.567
What's up with her?

389
00:19:10.651 --> 00:19:13.028
She's freaked out 'cause
she thinks Derek might be cheating on her.

390
00:19:13.111 --> 00:19:14.404
The one-year rule?

391
00:19:15.697 --> 00:19:16.865
It happens.

392
00:19:17.824 --> 00:19:19.451
Dude. it's real?

393
00:19:19.535 --> 00:19:20.577
Yeah.

394
00:19:21.078 --> 00:19:22.329
- Come on! Who's pumped?
- Yes!

395
00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:24.915
Me! I'm pumped. You pumped?

396
00:19:24.998 --> 00:19:26.333
- What's soccer?
- I'm pumped!

397
00:19:26.416 --> 00:19:28.961
- You pumped!
- Wait for me. wait for me.

398
00:19:31.421 --> 00:19:35.634
Are we early. or does everybody
just hate soccer as much as I do?

399
00:19:36.218 --> 00:19:38.428
Hey. I have a fun way to pass the time.

400
00:19:39.012 --> 00:19:41.265
I had Brian look at your new will.

401
00:19:41.932 --> 00:19:45.143
And he said it's more complicated
to become each other's beneficiaries

402
00:19:45.227 --> 00:19:46.395
than we think.

403
00:19:46.895 --> 00:19:49.314
We gotta get that power of attorney
straightened out too.

404
00:19:50.274 --> 00:19:52.943
When it comes time to pull the plug on me.

405
00:19:53.026 --> 00:19:56.238
I'm pretty sure
Meg's gonna chicken out. So...

406
00:19:57.698 --> 00:20:00.200
- you're my girl.
- I can't wait.

407
00:20:00.284 --> 00:20:02.452
- Can't wait for what?
- When I have to put Paul down.

408
00:20:03.203 --> 00:20:04.872
Cool. Let's get lunch after.

409
00:20:04.955 --> 00:20:05.998
Holy Macanoli.

410
00:20:06.081 --> 00:20:08.041
Look at all these beautiful faces.

411
00:20:08.125 --> 00:20:11.044
Thanks for coming. everyone.
I just want to say--

412
00:20:11.128 --> 00:20:14.006
- Not every moment is a speech moment.
- This one is.

413
00:20:14.089 --> 00:20:16.133
It still feels like a good lesson for you.

414
00:20:16.842 --> 00:20:19.303
Look. it means the world.
Y'all showing up like this.

415
00:20:19.928 --> 00:20:23.140
I'm not sure Alice would be such a strong
young woman if it weren't for all of you.

416
00:20:23.223 --> 00:20:24.433
She wouldn't be.

417
00:20:24.516 --> 00:20:26.476
- We did most of it.
- You did nothing.

418
00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:28.729
What the fuck?
I'm trying to say thank you.

419
00:20:28.812 --> 00:20:30.689
Great speech. Jimbo. Sit down.

420
00:20:30.772 --> 00:20:32.316
Hey. man. I heard Alice got her hair cut.

421
00:20:32.399 --> 00:20:33.942
so you might have to show me
which one she is.

422
00:20:34.026 --> 00:20:35.027
No problem.

423
00:20:35.861 --> 00:20:37.946
- I love you.
- Sean.

424
00:20:38.030 --> 00:20:39.198
You told people?

425
00:20:39.281 --> 00:20:40.908
Only Sean. babe.

426
00:20:42.117 --> 00:20:43.869
I love you too. man.

427
00:20:44.536 --> 00:20:46.622
And everybody else. I'm sorry. babe.

428
00:20:47.372 --> 00:20:48.874
Hey! Come on. Alice! Let's go!

429
00:20:48.957 --> 00:20:50.250
Come on. Alice!

430
00:20:50.334 --> 00:20:51.418
You're not cheering?

431
00:20:51.502 --> 00:20:52.961
She's just stretching.

432
00:20:53.045 --> 00:20:55.547
- Stretching like a beast!
- Hey.

433
00:20:55.631 --> 00:20:57.841
- Don't say beast. No.
- Yeah. Don't call women beasts. dude.

434
00:20:57.925 --> 00:21:00.636
A beast is a good thing in sports.

435
00:21:01.386 --> 00:21:02.387
- It is? Our bad.
- Our bad.

436
00:21:06.683 --> 00:21:08.936
Go. Alice!

437
00:21:09.019 --> 00:21:10.687
Wait. Why aren't you out there?

438
00:21:10.771 --> 00:21:13.315
The coach suggested
I might be better as a fan.

439
00:21:13.398 --> 00:21:16.401
Shut up!
Every coach I ever had said that to me.

440
00:21:17.778 --> 00:21:19.738
Okay. Let's go. Alice!

441
00:21:25.327 --> 00:21:29.915
Okay. okay. All right. Go. go. go.

442
00:21:31.542 --> 00:21:32.751
Yes. great pass.

443
00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:37.923
Okay. Hey! That was a great idea. Alice.

444
00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:40.759
- She likes it when I stay positive.
- Well. I'm not you.

445
00:21:40.843 --> 00:21:45.514
Hey. ponytail! When Alice gives you
a good pass. finish it! Yeah. you!

446
00:21:45.597 --> 00:21:48.350
- Jesus. Paul.
- Hey. Paul. Just tone it down.

447
00:21:49.059 --> 00:21:50.894
Let's go. Alice! Come on. girl!

448
00:21:50.978 --> 00:21:53.480
- Come on. girl!
- That's it. Come on. Alice!

449
00:21:53.564 --> 00:21:57.067
- Come on. You've got this game!
- Yeah. Yes. yes. yes. yes. yes.

450
00:21:58.277 --> 00:22:00.070
God! That's a foul!

451
00:22:00.153 --> 00:22:01.363
- Play on!
- Come on. ref.

452
00:22:01.446 --> 00:22:03.198
What game are you watching?

453
00:22:03.282 --> 00:22:05.075
Pull your head out of your ass!

454
00:22:05.158 --> 00:22:07.244
Oh. my gosh. We are so cute.

455
00:22:07.911 --> 00:22:09.705
Go. sweetie. Go. go. go.

456
00:22:12.791 --> 00:22:14.209
That's all right.

457
00:22:14.293 --> 00:22:18.046
Hey. You're a doctor. right?
I'm having so much trouble focusing.

458
00:22:18.130 --> 00:22:19.423
I'm not giving you Adderall.

459
00:22:25.262 --> 00:22:27.806
Hey. don't touch my little girl.

460
00:22:29.850 --> 00:22:31.894
- Good call. ref. Thank you. ref.
- Yeah! Finally. finally.

461
00:22:31.977 --> 00:22:33.520
Nice and calm. sweetie.

462
00:22:39.193 --> 00:22:41.403
Wait. wait. Hey. everybody.

463
00:22:41.987 --> 00:22:43.655
I need you to do what I do. okay?

464
00:22:50.078 --> 00:22:51.288
Okay. like that.

465
00:23:12.017 --> 00:23:14.728
Goal!

466
00:23:17.981 --> 00:23:19.733
- Amazing game.
- Hey. you played awesome too.

467
00:23:19.816 --> 00:23:20.817
Thanks.

468
00:23:20.901 --> 00:23:25.822
Alice. Alice. Alice.

469
00:23:25.906 --> 00:23:27.115
Okay. it's getting weird now.

470
00:23:27.199 --> 00:23:29.117
Hey. Alice. You have a second?

471
00:23:29.201 --> 00:23:31.161
- Sure.
- Is that the Wesleyan coach?

472
00:23:31.245 --> 00:23:33.205
- Don't look.
- I don't give a shit.

473
00:23:33.872 --> 00:23:34.998
I'm staring her down.

474
00:23:35.582 --> 00:23:36.583
Alice Laird.

475
00:23:39.419 --> 00:23:40.921
- Do you wanna just.
- Paul. Paul.

476
00:23:41.004 --> 00:23:43.715
I feel like that's the exact
wrong approach for this moment.

477
00:23:45.425 --> 00:23:47.803
So if you two are definitely switching
your power of attorney.

478
00:23:47.886 --> 00:23:50.222
I'd also recommend updating your 401(k)s.

479
00:23:50.305 --> 00:23:53.433
and getting Julie on the deed
to your condo. which is a tricky process.

480
00:23:53.517 --> 00:23:57.104
You need a notary. and a witness.
and the whisker of a snow leopard.

481
00:23:57.187 --> 00:23:59.731
What do I have to sign
to get you to stop talking?

482
00:23:59.815 --> 00:24:01.733
Hey! You asked me. Grumpus.

483
00:24:01.817 --> 00:24:06.363
Ignore him. It's all just... I don't know...
Just feels so complicated.

484
00:24:06.446 --> 00:24:08.115
What if you two just got married?

485
00:24:08.824 --> 00:24:10.325
Wouldn't that take care most of this?

486
00:24:11.243 --> 00:24:13.412
You know. he's not wrong.

487
00:24:14.371 --> 00:24:17.416
I mean. what little girl
hasn't dreamed of getting married.

488
00:24:17.499 --> 00:24:19.585
so that she has fewer forms to fill out.

489
00:24:20.377 --> 00:24:21.503
Yeah. that would do it.

